-- Surkov Seen as Chief of Staff in New Government, Kommersant Says
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-05-15T05:16:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/surkov-seen-as-chief-of-staff-in-new-government-kommersant-says.html
Russian Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev is expected to keep  Vladislav Surkov  in his current
position of Deputy Prime Minister and name him to the post of
Chief of Staff,  Kommersant   reported , citing two unidentified
people close to the government.  Medvedev met with Surkov on Monday to discuss the makeup of
the new government and is expected to submit his proposals to
President Vladimir Putin today, according to the Moscow-based
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
 jrudnitsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
